{
  "texts": [
    "Since all jailbreaking prompts in our dataset are significantly shorter than 2,000 tokens, the observed safety enhancements in the pruned models cannot be attributed to a reduction in effective context length.",
    "We evaluated the models' resistance to generating harmful content by comparing the jailbreaking success rates across several models, as shown in Figure 3, Figure 7, and Figure 8.",
    "Across the five categories of malicious tasks, we observe significant variations in jailbreaking success rates between models.",
    "Mistral emerges as the most vulnerable, often failing to refuse any malicious task in some categories.",
    "In contrast, LLaMA-2 Chat demonstrates the highest resilience."
  ]
}